crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is identified as a component of NetSupport Manager, a legitimate remote administration tool (RAT), based on the imported function `_NSMClient32@8` and the embedded manifest string `<description>NetSupport Manager Remote Control.</description>`. While NetSupport Manager is a legitimate application, it is frequently abused by threat actors for unauthorized remote access and post-exploitation activities. The presence of this tool outside of a managed IT environment is highly suspicious.
